metadata.name: Quasi Prism #2

Press "s" to download the current frame as a .png file.

Each rectangle has a random color blending mode so you'll see interesting interactions on overlaps.


From simple rules emerge complex, detailed, and varied patterns.

metadata.name: Specter of Fears #146
metadata.description:
In the dreamlike landscape of our minds, the specter of fears is like a wraith, ever-present and ethereal. It whispers in our ear, reminding us of all the things we dare not face. It is a shadow that falls across our hearts, casting a pall of doubt and uncertainty. But even as it haunts us, we must remember that it is a part of us. We must learn to accept its presence, and to use it to our advantage. For fear is not always a curse, it is a guide that shows us where we must grow stronger. It is a companion that walks with us through the dark night, illuminating the path ahead. By embracing our fears, we find the courage to face them, and to overcome them. We find the strength to live fully, to love fiercely, and to pursue our dreams with abandon.

Controls :

• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

Specter of Fears by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2023
Made with Unity

metadata.name: La Pedrera Serie 1 #195
metadata.description:
This project is inspired from Gaudí's Casa Milà in Barcelona, also known as La Pedrera. 

This is the first part of a 2-part-serie based on La Pedrera.

In this project, which is intentionaly saturated in color, you will recognize an abstract reproduction of the curved floors and windows of La Casa Milà.

The colors are accentued by the flowers disseminated on each floor. 

Main features of this project include:
- Palette: 10 colors,
- Texture: Strong or Soft,
- Noise: True or False,
- Strong Lines: True or False,
- Flower Packing: Mini or Maxi.

In live mode, press [s] to save a 1200 x 1500 (4 DPI) version of the mint.

Thanks a lot to everyone who will mint a token! :)

metadata.name: Landscapes in my mind #85
metadata.description:
In this work I tried to convey the idea of a landscape (many landscapes) with hills, trees, grass, bushes, skies and clouds. As is normal on fxhash I have accomplished all this by writing the code that generates the elements in a scene.
While writing the code to obtain these landscapes I did not try to reproduce landscapes seen in reality or in photography, rather I followed from time to time ideas of landscapes that came to my mind as a sort of lucid dream. I hope I managed to convey this idea of a landscape that is halfway between reality and fantasy.

Lands and Clouds are rendered using a mix of simplex noise and FBM (Fractional Brownian Motion), trees are generated with recursive functions an placed using Poisson Disk Sampling distribution. The distribution density could be homogeneous (land heightmap drive the density) or biased to have more density towards the top, bottom, left or right of the land.


Developed with p5.js using WEBGL renderer.
Rendering is faster with chrome browser.

[1] to render at 1600x1600
[2] to render at 2400x2400
[3] to render at 3200x3200
[s] to save a png at last rendered resolution.


Features:
"LandPalette": 20 colormaps
"TreePalette": 20 colormaps
"Light":  Morning, Evening, Night
"SkyColor": Blue, Azure, Turquoise, Gray, VioletRed
"Haze": True, False
"Rainbow":  True, False
"Grayscale": True, False
"TreeDensity": Homogeneous, Top, Bottom, Left, Right


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Vissen #17
metadata.description:
Scribbled patterns. An exploration of colour and texture.

Press 's' to save an image.

If you want to increase the resolution of the saved image, add e.g. &size=2000 after the live/fullscreen view URL to render the canvas at that specific width (default = browser sized)

Add e.g. &ratio=1.2 to render at a different aspect ratio, like 1.2:1 (this will produce a visually different yet thematically similar output, default = 1.4)

metadata.name: string_pllu #21
metadata.description:
Making some abstract plants, inspired by a painting technique called string pull.

Connect some random semi circles with strings and pull the strings from the bottom of the canvas.

The semi circles rotate while moving to create some random brush strokes.

metadata.name: Whisper #262
metadata.description:
Abstract forms built with noise and texture

-------------

A note on rendering times: *Whisper has a lot going on*. It can take up to 1-5 minutes to fully render, depending on your hardware configuration, including a 15sec-1min loading phase during which lots of calculations take place (but no visuals). It'll get there, just be patient! A small loading bar along the bottom also shows the progression of the render during the drawing phase.

Press 'S' or click "Save image" to save a PNG version of the artwork while in full-screen/IPFS view

Customisation
-------------

The following parameters can be adjusted in full-screen mode.
Open the token in full-screen/IPFS mode, and add any of these to the URL:

&size=2000 (replace 2000 with any value up to around 8000) - this sets the resolution/width of the canvas in pixels. Use this to generate very large PNG images (50MB+) suitable for printing at large DPI & canvas sizes. The max value here is dependent on your hardware, might not work on mobiles etc.

&ratio=1.4 (any value between 1 and 2, default = 1.4) - set the aspect ratio of the work. By default Whisper renders at 1:1.4 but you can change this to match other printing formats. Different ratios will produce slightly different outputs, but the overall character of the artwork should still be present. Landscape mode is not supported.
